description.p:
The device according to the invention therefore:


allows autonomous operation without any external supply of energy (mechanical system);


limits the rate of flow of fuel (in the case of the aeronautical application) to, at most, the flow rate level that corresponds to the maximum permissible thrust;


allows the flow rate demanded for take-off thrust increased by 15% (ageing) "at sea level" to be supplied, when the booster pumps are in operation;


does not act as a point where debris has an increased likelihood of accumulating;


can be tested periodically and with ease.
